### HYMN XIX

#### A prayer for protection from arrows and for the punishment of enemies

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0101901">1</span></span>Let not the
piercers find us, nor let those who wound discover  
   us.  
  O Indra, make the arrows fall, turned, far from us, to every  
   side.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0101902">2</span></span>Turned from
us let the arrows fall, those shot and those that will  
   be shot.  
  Shafts of the Gods and shafts of men, strike and transfix mine  
   enemies:  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0101903">3</span></span>Whoever
treateth us as foes, be he our own or strange to us, a  
   kinsman or a foreigner,  
  May Rudra with his arrows pierce and slay these enemies of  
   mine. <span id="page_a19">p. a19</span>  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0101904">4</span></span>The rival
and non-rival, he who in his hatred curses us  
  May all the deities injure him! My nearest, closest mail is  
   prayer.

